# Gitignored files a fresh worktree needs, copied from the primary checkout.
# One path/glob per line; `#` comments and blank lines ignored. Globs are
# expanded against the primary worktree; zero matches is fine.
#
# Consumed by two paths that must stay in parity:
#   - dotagents' WorktreeCreate hook (the EnterWorktree / `--worktree` / subagent path)
#   - scripts/worktree-init.sh (the manual `git worktree add` path)
#
# COPY only — never list node_modules/.venv/dist/caches here. This is a Python
# repo whose .venv must be a REAL `python -m venv` install (its bin/activate
# hardcode the worktree path), so the venv is bootstrapped by worktree-init.sh,
# never copied or symlinked.

# Local secrets/config the Django app reads (app/settings.py -> load_dotenv(".env.local")).
# Normalized on `.env.local` for fleet consistency; the `.env.*.local` glob is the
# fleet convention and harmless here (it matches nothing).
.env.local
.env.*.local
